                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13289075" author="djencks" created="Tue, 5 Jun 2012 01:45:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Suggestion on how to split spec and non-spec behavior to make it clearer what is required for spec behavior.  Also includes determining which state is the satsified state by returning from the class rather than using a switch statement, which is a separate change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13289355" author="fmeschbe" created="Tue, 5 Jun 2012 11:50:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The one thing I don&apos;t like about the patch is that the m_componentInstances field is changed to be protected. I would really like to keep this private if possible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; determining which state is the satsified state&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have been contemplating something along these lines, too. So I am ok with this change&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, +1 to apply this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13289850" author="djencks" created="Tue, 5 Jun 2012 23:31:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I made m_componentInstances private again, good idea, and committed in rev 1346660.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13501054" author="fmeschbe" created="Tue, 20 Nov 2012 10:58:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Close after release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
